bersetzung sowie ein sprachlicher und sachlicher Kommentar.  a“Spuria Macri” consists of 20 chapters and 487 hexameters about plant, animal, and mineral remedies added to the poem “Macer Floridus.” This translation, the first ever into German, contains rich commentaries on language, sources, reception, authorship, intellectual history, and genre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aMateria medicavEarly works to 1800. 4aLehrgedicht. 4aMedizingeschichte. 4aMittelalter. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aDidactic poetry.  aMiddle Ages.  ahistory of medicine.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUMSWISS. 2013z9783110317091oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311030849540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030859440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110308594423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110308594/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGDb2013  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014